node.text:
Invisible Wounds: Recovery and Resilience
.
Everyone is susceptible to invisible wounds. Being able to recognize one of these wounds, and using positive language when discussing it, supports a positive culture across the Department of the Air Force and could save a life. It is important for Airmen and Guardians to seek help for invisible wounds, taking that first step towards recovery.
.
This video describes the importance of Airmen and Guardians seeking help for invisible wounds and how taking that first step towards recovery results in positive outcomes and enhanced resilience.
.
#InvisibleWounds #MentalHealthAwarenessMonth

node.text:
Invisible Wounds: Risk, Impact, and Available Resources
.
Over the past five years, United States Department of the Air Force’s Invisible Wounds Initiative has implemented solutions that drive timely, proactive case handling, equitable, informed interactions and decisions, engaged leadership and a supportive environment, and accessible, effective care delivery. 
.
Everyone is susceptible to invisible wounds. The impact of invisible wounds and can develop at any time, in any place, in or out of uniform.
.
Learn more at: https://go.usa.gov/xszpN
.
#InvisibleWounds #MentalHealthAwarenessMonth

node.title: Invisible Wounds: Risk, Impact, and Available Resources

node.text:
Invisible Wounds: Signs and Symptoms
.
Since its inception in 2016, the United States Department of the Air Force’s Invisible Wounds Initiative has been a leader in creating a supportive culture for #Airmen living with invisible wounds. Being able to recognize an invisible wound could save a life. Airman can learn to see the signs and symptoms of invisible wounds in others that they may see in themselves.
.
#InvisibleWounds #MentalHealthAwarenessMonth

node.text:
Air Force Chief of Staff Gen. Charles Q. Brown, Jr., & @cmsaf_official discuss how empowering Airmen will lead to success in building the future Air Force today. They also discussed Accelerate Change or Lose, the Action Orders, leadership and followership, how to rise above bias & self-limitations, and the future of the #AirForce.
.
The primary focus of this call was to connect with Airmen across the world, and give insight to how the Action orders, new Air Force missions statement and developmental guidance are being implemented for the Total Force.
.
#RealTalk #CoffeeTalk #Future #Empowerment #Questions

node.text:
Airman 1st Class Aaron Rasmussen, 908th Expeditionary Air Refueling Squadron boom operator, prepares to refuel a @usnavy F/A-18 Hornet aircraft over Afghanistan during an aerial refueling mission, supporting the non-combatant evacuation of the area. 
.
@usafcent #refuel #aircraft #flag 
.
📸  by TSgt Michelle Y. Alvarez

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on September 11, 2021. May be an image of skyscraper and text that says 'NEVER FORGET. 9-11-01'.

node.text:
Today, we recognize Patriot Day and remember the thousands of lives lost on Sept. 11, 2001. 
.
We acknowledge—with profound gratitude and appreciation—the sacrifices of all the brave, selfless heroes who tirelessly defend our freedom.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on September 10, 2021. May be an image of 3 people, military uniform and text that says 'Please join US for a VIRTUAL TOWN HALL discussing the RACIAL DISPARITY REVIEW UPDATE 16 September 2021 1:30PM EDT USAirForce SRNE ETO FENTES SpaceForceDoD'.

node.text:
Join Department of the Air Force senior leaders on Facebook for a virtual town hall discussing the Racial Disparity Review next Thursday, Sept. 16 at 1:30 p.m. EDT.
.
The Racial Disparity Review and second disparity review were released recently, and if you have questions about these two topics, there will be opportunities to get answers for questions you may have.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on September 09, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and outdoors.

node.text:
Master Sgt. Jason Livingston and Airman 1st Class Jolan Besse, 535th Airlift Squadron loadmasters, sit on the ramp of a C-17 Globemaster III during a familiarization flight for the Pacific Air Forces’ Senior Enlisted Leadership Summit at Joint Base Pearl Harbor Hickam-Hawaii.
.
Senior leaders from the Indo-Pacific region gathered as part of Pacific Air Chiefs Symposium 2021 to build mutual understanding of varied regional perspectives. 
.
#airpower #aircraft #ocean #enlisted #pacific
.
📸  by SSgt Hailey Haux

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by U.S. Air Force on September 08, 2021. May be an image of airplane and sky.

node.text:
B-52s from @teambarksdale integrated with the Indonesian Air Force during a Bomber Task Force mission. This is a first for the aircraft. 
.
BTF missions demonstrate the credibility of U.S. forces to address a diverse and uncertain security environment. 
.
#bomber #exercise #aircraft #b52 #militaryphotography

node.text:
Learning the "Why" 
.
Secretary of the Air Force Frank Kendall directed the COVID-19 vaccine implementation guidelines recently for Department of the Air Force military members.
.
Over the next few weeks, we will be diving into the stories of nine different Airmen and how they were affected by #COVID19. Hear Chief Master Sgt. Casy Boomershine's reasons for leading from the front.
.
#family #vaccine #COVID19 #militarylife #military

node.text:
Staff Sgt. Codee Tubb, 435th Security Forces Squadron contingency member, sits on top of a turret at Cheshnegirovo Air Base, Bulgaria. Airmen and Bulgarian armed forces participated in a multinational exercise in order to improve overall coordination and professional relationships. 
.
#sunsetphotography #militarypolice #securityforces
.
📸 by SrA Thomas Karol

node.text:
Undersecretary of the Air Force Gina Ortiz Jones sat down to share her priorities in a recent interview. Hear how she is working to remove barriers and biases so that the best can serve in their full capacity while posturing for the pacing challenge; ultimately, working as one team to champion a culture of success.
.
#airpower #airforce #spaceforce #success #priorities

A fire suppression system using rapid-expanding foam is tested in a hangar at Sumpter Smith Joint National Guard Base, Alabama. The more environmentally-friendly foam creates a blanket to suppress and extinguish fires, to keep aircraft maintainers working safe. @airnationalguard

Moment of clarity ⛅️ 
.
Airman 1st Class Andrew Harris, a 39th Airlift Squadron C-130J #SuperHercules loadmaster from @dyess_afb, Texas, looks through the aircraft’s rear vision device during a RED FLAG-Alaska 21-3 sortie over the Joint Pacific Alaska Range Complex.
.
RF-A 21-3 is a Pacific Air Forces-sponsored exercise designed to provide realistic training in a simulated combat environment providing joint offensive counter-air, interdiction, close air support, and large force employment training. 
.
📸 by A1C Patrick Sullivan
.
#militaryphotography #loadmaster #USAF

Today is Labor Day. This holiday is an annual celebration of the social and economic achievements of American workers. 
.
The American worker has raised the nation’s standard of living and contributed to the greatest production the world has ever known and the labor movement has brought us closer to the realization of our traditional ideals of economic and political democracy.
